# CVE-2026-12151 / GHSA-vxpw-j846-p89q — undici WebSocket DoS, HIGH.
# Accepted 2026-06-22; review by 2026-09-22.
#
# Evidence: Trivy located undici 6.25.0 at
# /usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm/node_modules/undici/package.json in the
# node:24-slim runtime image. It is shipped by the base image's global npm, not
# by BudgetSpin's package-lock.json. Production starts with `node` directly and
# never invokes npm. A repository search also found no use of `new WebSocket`,
# `WebSocketStream`, or ws:// / wss:// endpoints. The upstream advisory requires
# one of those client APIs to connect to an attacker-controlled or compromised
# WebSocket endpoint, so the vulnerable path is not reachable in BudgetSpin.
# Reassess if runtime startup or outbound networking changes, or at expiry.
CVE-2026-12151 exp:2026-09-22
